Day 17 – CSS Position and Display

position determines how elements are placed:

static → default.

relative → relative to normal position.

absolute → relative to nearest positioned ancestor.

fixed → fixed on screen while scrolling.
display controls layout: block, inline, inline-block, flex, grid, none.
Example:

div { position: absolute; top: 50px; left: 100px; }
p { display: inline; }


These properties help align and organize elements on the page.
